01:04.339 --> 01:09.947
In fact, in Vivian's case, her unit of production isn't the tangible hours she works.

01:10.489 --> 01:13.999
It's the intangible difference she makes during that one hour of work.

01:14.557 --> 01:18.341
This is Dave Arringdale who's actually been a longtime guest at Vivian's motel.

01:18.476 --> 01:21.955
He stayed there a hundred times in the last 20 years.

01:22.381 --> 01:25.205
And he's loyal to the property because of the relationship....

01:25.493 --> 01:27.808
...that Vivian and her fellow employees have created with him.

01:28.091 --> 01:30.981
They've created a habitat of happiness for Dave.

01:31.397 --> 01:38.374
And he tells me that he can always count on Vivian and the staff there to make him feel at home.

01:39.354 --> 01:45.991
Why is it that business leaders and investors quite often don't see the connection...

01:46.327 --> 01:49.745
